emonstrated, as well as decreased tumor incidence one to two years later (Roebuck et al., 1991). In rats treated with a single dose of 5 mg/kg AFB1, a progressive increase in the number and size of tigroid cell foci and neoplastic nodules was observed over a two-year period following dosing. Within these foci and nodules, the mitotic index was 100-fold higher than in the surrounding liver parenchyma (Bannasch et al., 1985).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:40:41 +0000 2026"}